From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000001 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Varun Shah <vash6799@colorado.edu>
Date: Fri, 11 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/3] drm/vc4: Add secondary telemetry overlay plane and custom IOCTL

Issue 5: Allocate a secondary non-primary hardware plane in the vc4 driver
         that is reserved for the telemetry HUD overlay.

Issue 6: Add DRM_IOCTL_VC4_TELEMETRY_OVERLAY which accepts a pre-rendered
         DRM framebuffer handle + telemetry metadata from userspace and
         programs the overlay plane at the specified screen position.

Architecture:
  Userspace orchestrator:
    1. Allocates a DRM dumb buffer (ARGB8888) sized for the HUD
    2. Maps it with mmap, renders text/indicators into pixel data
    3. Creates a DRM framebuffer from the dumb buffer handle
    4. Calls DRM_IOCTL_VC4_TELEMETRY_OVERLAY with the fb handle + data
  Kernel (this patch):
    5. Validates the framebuffer handle
    6. Finds the reserved TELEMETRY overlay plane
    7. Calls drm_atomic_helper to move/show the plane at x_pos, y_pos
    8. Commit the atomic state — plane appears on HDMI instantly

Signed-off-by: Varun Shah <vash6799@colorado.edu>
